<item>
            <title>[CXF-3214] CXFBusLifeCycleManager will call the preshutdown twice if when the BusApplicationContext is closed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3214</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I write the test of BusApplicationListenerTest I found the BusLifeCycleListener will be called twice when the application context is closed.&lt;br/&gt;
The code of CXFBusLifeCycleManager should be changed like this&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;--- rt/core/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/buslifecycle/CXFBusLifeCycleManager.java	(revision 1051771)
+++ rt/core/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/buslifecycle/CXFBusLifeCycleManager.java	(working copy)
@@ -78,9 +78,11 @@
     
     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void preShutdown() {
         &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// TODO inverse order of registration?
&lt;/span&gt;-        preShutdownCalled = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
-        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (BusLifeCycleListener listener : listeners) {
-            listener.preShutdown();
+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!preShutdownCalled) { 
+            preShutdownCalled = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
+            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (BusLifeCycleListener listener : listeners) {
+                listener.preShutdown();
+            }
         }
     }

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
